your_events_v2.name: Brookhaven Town Voting on New Fiber provider
your_events_v2.description: NOTICE IS HEREBY GIVEN that pursuant to Section 64 of Town Law, a public hearing will be held by the Town Board of the Town of Brookhaven at the Town Board Auditorium located at One Independence Hill, Second Floor, Farmingville, New York, and which will be streamed live over the internet at brookhavenny.gov/meeting, on March 30, 2023, at 5:30 P.M. to consider a License Agreement between the Town of Brookhaven and Optical Communications Group, Inc., for the purpose of operating a fiber-based internet network.

your_events_v2.name: Discussing the Broadband Monopoly (feat. Senator Michelle Hinchey NY-46)
your_events_v2.description:
Unlike the prior meeting with the Constituent Services Liaison, we've been invited to a followup meeting with Senator Hinchey herself!

We may have a guest appearance of Congressman Delgado's (NY-19) Chief of Staff.

The meeting will allow us the opportunity to discuss the Digital Divide, issues with current providers and the monopoly market.

your_events_v2.name: TSCFIS General Memebership Meeting - Casual Meet&Greet
your_events_v2.description:
If you'd like to join us, send a message and we'll provide the link.

We're inviting anyone who is interested in volunteering to join us for a membership meeting tonight. Tell us about yourself and how you'd like to contribute.

Skills we are currently looking for:
Web Design
Marketing
Writing/Journalism
Graphic Design
Brand Management

your_events_v2.name: TSCFIS LIVE! - Featuring Jessica Singleton, Liaison for NY-46
your_events_v2.description:
The Office of Senator Michelle Hinchey from NY-46 mentioned interest in hearing our case against Optimum and learning more about our group. We will be meeting with Jessica Singleton, Constituent Services Liaison tonight.

Thanks to Kathen Cowan, our local outreach rep from Ulster County for reaching out to the Senator's office.

This will be our first attempt at a livestream, let us know what you think of the format! Fingers crossed there aren't any technical issues.
